In the meantime we have, and treasure, your Middle Ages.1 Your text is robust, colorful, tremendously talented. From notes I made while reading it I see that I chuckled enthusiastically over the "intimate" insects (p. 78). Of the two wonderful paragraphs (p. 102) dealing with education, I noticed, without much surprise, that the female child received twice as much attention as the boy did. Yo